The paper discusses the use of lexical features in coreference resolution, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) falling under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the limitations of relying solely on lexical features, which is a common issue in machine learning (cs.AI) and can affect the generalization of models (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the evaluation of coreference resolution models, which can fall under the category of natural language understanding (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) if the models are evaluated on visual data.
